<emphasis bold="true" box="[861,991,1195,1218]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Oedothorax</emphasis>
Bertkau in 
<bibRefCitation author="Forster A. &amp; Bertkau P." box="[1127,1406,1195,1220]" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen des Naturhistorischen Vereins der Preussischen Rheinlande und Westfalens" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="205 - 278" part="40" refString="Forster A., Bertkau P. 1883. Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Spinnenfauna der Rheinprovinz. Verhandlungen des Naturhistorischen Vereins der Preussischen Rheinlande und Westfalens 40: 205 - 278." title="Beitrage zur Kenntniss der Spinnenfauna der Rheinprovinz" type="journal article" year="1883">FÃ¶rster &amp; Bertkau, 1883</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[831,1437,1242,1721]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
The genus has an almost cosmopolitan distribution and is represented in the Palaearctic by 44 species, in the Afrotropics by 10, in the 
<collectingRegion box="[1198,1285,1308,1331]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Oriental</collectingRegion>
by nine, and in the Nearctic by seven species (based mostly on the World Spider Catalogue, 2016). A single record of an 
<taxonomicName box="[831,958,1405,1428]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[831,958,1405,1428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from the Neotropics, i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1902" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuegianus">
<emphasis box="[1302,1437,1406,1430]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">O. fuegianus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon E." box="[839,982,1438,1462]" journalOrPublisher="Acariden und Gonyleptiden. Ergebnisse der Hamburger Magalhaensische Sammelreise (Hamburg) 6" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 47" part="4" refString="Simon E. 1902. Arachnoideen, excl. Acariden und Gonyleptiden. Ergebnisse der Hamburger Magalhaensische Sammelreise (Hamburg) 6 (4): 1 - 47." title="Arachnoideen, excl" type="journal article" year="1902">Simon, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1401,1438,1461]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Argentina</collectingCountry>
on the basis on a single female (
<bibRefCitation author="Simon E." box="[1134,1274,1470,1495]" journalOrPublisher="Acariden und Gonyleptiden. Ergebnisse der Hamburger Magalhaensische Sammelreise (Hamburg) 6" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 47" part="4" refString="Simon E. 1902. Arachnoideen, excl. Acariden und Gonyleptiden. Ergebnisse der Hamburger Magalhaensische Sammelreise (Hamburg) 6 (4): 1 - 47." title="Arachnoideen, excl" type="journal article" year="1902">Simon, 1902</bibRefCitation>
), is regarded as a misidentification (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller J. A." box="[1086,1222,1503,1528]" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="1 - 263" part="149" refString="Miller J. A. 2007. Review of erigonine spider genera in the Neotropics (Araneae: Linyphiidae, Erigoninae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 149 (Suppl. 1): 1 - 263." title="Review of erigonine spider genera in the Neotropics (Araneae: Linyphiidae, Erigoninae)" type="journal article" year="2007">Miller, 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[831,1437,1242,1721]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
In the following, I present a new 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1347,1535,1558]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Oedothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1220,1347,1535,1558]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Oedothorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from the Indian Himalayas. This species is very similar to an Afrotropical congener, known from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1281,1382,1601,1625]" name="Comoros" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Comoros</collectingCountry>
, and, like 
<taxonomicName box="[881,1144,1633,1656]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Enguterothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simpulum">
<emphasis box="[881,1144,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Enguterothrix simpulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above), demonstrates close relations between Afrotropical and 
<collectingRegion box="[1349,1436,1665,1688]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Oriental</collectingRegion>
linyphiid faunas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
